In a fit of rage the townsfolk rose up against the suspected vandals, a pair of foolhardy teens always looking for trouble.
The teens protested their innocence but of course no one believed them. In the face of the angry mob, the teens had no choice but to leave the town, never to return again. 
However, the day after they left, the denizens of the town felt the first gust of a stormy wind in a long time, and many swore they heard the whispers of Jimmy in the wind, "It was not them". 

